# Quickstart

## Writing Content

Create `.rdx` files in the `docs/` directory. RDX is Markdown with embedded components:

```rdx
<Callout kind="warning" title="Heads up">
  Components are embedded directly in your Markdown content.
</Callout>
```

<Callout kind="warning" title="Heads up">
Components are embedded directly in your Markdown content.
</Callout>

## Available Components

### Callout

Display info, warnings, errors, or tips:

```rdx
<Callout kind="info" title="Note">
  Your message here.
</Callout>
```

<Callout kind="info" title="Note">
Your message here.
</Callout>

Variants: `info`, `warning`, `error`, `tip`

### Tabs

Group content into switchable tabs:

```rdx
<Tabs>
  <Tab title="npm">
    npm install oxidoc
  </Tab>
  <Tab title="yarn">
    yarn add oxidoc
  </Tab>
  <Tab title="pnpm">
    pnpm add oxidoc
  </Tab>
</Tabs>
```

<Tabs>
<Tab title="npm">
npm install oxidoc
</Tab>
<Tab title="yarn">
yarn add oxidoc
</Tab>
<Tab title="pnpm">
pnpm add oxidoc
</Tab>
</Tabs>

### CodeBlock

Code with syntax highlighting, filename header, and copy button:

```rdx
<CodeBlock language="rust" filename="main.rs" highlight="2">
  fn main() {
      println!("Hello, Oxidoc!");
  }
</CodeBlock>
```

<CodeBlock language="rust" filename="main.rs" highlight="2">
fn main() {
    println!("Hello, Oxidoc!");
}
</CodeBlock>

### Accordion

Collapsible content sections:

```rdx
<Accordion title="Click to expand">
  Hidden content goes here.
</Accordion>
```

<Accordion title="Click to expand">
Hidden content goes here.
</Accordion>

### CardGrid

Responsive grid of linked cards:

```rdx
<CardGrid>
  <Card title="First" href="/page-1">
    Description here.
  </Card>
  <Card title="Second" href="/page-2">
    Another card.
  </Card>
</CardGrid>
```

<CardGrid>
<Card title="First">Description here.</Card>
<Card title="Second">Another card.</Card>
</CardGrid>

## Development Server

Run `oxidoc dev` to start a local server with hot reload:

```bash
oxidoc dev
```

Edit any `.rdx` file and the browser refreshes automatically.

## Building for Production

```bash
oxidoc build
```

Your site is generated in `dist/` — deploy it anywhere.
